Class UrlMatcherFactory

Factory for UrlMatcher instances.

The factory is available to ng1 services as $urlMatcherFactor or ng1 providers as $urlMatcherFactoryProvider.

  • type(name: string, definition?: ParamTypeDefinition, definitionFn?: function): any

  • Creates and registers a custom ParamType object

  • Creates and registers a custom ParamType object

    A ParamType can be used to generate URLs with typed parameters.

    Parameters

    • name string
      :

      The type name.

    • definition: Optional  ParamTypeDefinition
      :

      The type definition. See ParamTypeDefinition for information on the values accepted.

    • definitionFn: Optional  function
      :

      A function that is injected before the app runtime starts. The result of this function should be a ParamTypeDefinition. The result is merged into the existing definition. See ParamType for information on the values accepted.

        • (): ParamTypeDefinition

        • Returns ParamTypeDefinition

    Returns any

    :
    • if a type was registered: the UrlMatcherFactory
      • if only the name parameter was specified: the currently registered ParamType object, or undefined

    Note: Register custom types before using them in a state definition.

    See ParamTypeDefinition for examples
